timeline
    title Four Generations of Tactile Robotics (1965-2026)
    section Gen 1 — Discrete Taxels (1965-1995)
        1965 : First tactile array sensor (SRI)
        1975 : Capacitive tactile skin (CMU)
        1985 : Piezoresistive arrays for grippers
        1995 : Commercial force/torque sensors (ATI)
    section Gen 2 — Multimodal Arrays (1995-2015)
        2000 : BioTac multimodal fingertip (SynTouch)
        2005 : Large-area tactile skin (iCub)
        2010 : Flexible MEMS tactile sensors
        2015 : Commercial tactile grippers (Robotiq)
    section Gen 3 — Vision-Based Touch (2015-2023)
        2017 : GelSight high-res optical sensor (MIT)
        2020 : DIGIT compact sensor (Meta FAIR)
        2021 : GelSight Wedge / ReSkin (MIT / Meta)
        2022 : TACTO simulator / GelSlim 3.0
    section Gen 4 — Foundation Models + Dexterous Hands (2023-2026)
        2024 : Digit 360 multimodal fingertip (Meta)
        2024 : AnySkin modular tactile (CMU)
        2025 : Sparsh tactile foundation model (Meta)
        2025 : F-TAC Hand / Bunny-VisionPro (Peking U.)
        2026 : VLA + tactile integration era
